A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 2 of Chapter 7 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to the imposition, rate, computation, exemptions, and credits for state income tax,
3 so as to increase the amount of tax credits available for the rehabilitation of certified
4 structures; to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date and applicability;
5 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 2 of Chapter 7 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
9 imposition, rate, computation, exemptions, and credits for state income tax, is amended by
10 revising subsection (c) of Code Section 48-7-29.8, relating to tax credits for the rehabilitation
11 of historic structures, as follows:
12 "(c)(1) In no event shall credits for a historic home exceed $100,000.00 in any 120 month
13 period.
14 (2) The maximum credit for any other individual certified structure shall be $5
15 $7.5 million for any taxable year, except in the case that the project creates 200 or more
16 full-time, permanent jobs or $5 million in annual payroll within two years of the placed
